  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In the elaboration phase, the focus remains twofold. One emphasis is on gaining a deeper understanding of the&#xD;
    architectural and design constraints imposed on the candidate solutions by any infrastructure on which the solution&#xD;
    will run and any other systems with which the solution must interact. The second focus is on refining any potential&#xD;
    architectural alternatives that may affect the candidate solutions in order to ensure that the implications are fully&#xD;
    understood.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It may be necessary to prototype critical external interfaces or design mechanisms that are new to the team. It may&#xD;
    also be necessary to prototype how the architecture responds to specific quality attributes such as reusability,&#xD;
    security, or scalability. Exploratory throwaway prototypes are used to mitigate specific risks in addition to the &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/workproducts/cots_executing_system_C8925279.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{2179F9CD-7406-4BDC-921D-D27384146E31}&quot;>Executing System&lt;/a> (called executable architectural prototype in&#xD;
    elaboration) that is built later in the iteration.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The important areas of work in this sphere are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Refine the architectural context:&lt;/b> The purpose is to refine the architectural context for the solution in&#xD;
        sufficient detail to ensure that each candidate solution developed in response to the identified stakeholder needs&#xD;
        will operate in the context of the larger organization. This also involves refining architecture constraints,&#xD;
        boundaries and interfaces posed by external systems with which the solution must interface. This information is&#xD;
        captured in the To-Be &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Models&lt;/a> and To-Be &lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Documents&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Refine architectural alternatives:&lt;/b> The purpose is to refine the potential architectural alternatives that&#xD;
        may affect the candidate solutions. This is done by detailing the To-Be &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Model&lt;/a> and To-Be &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Document&lt;/a>. For instance, some architectural&#xD;
        alternative could be refined by applying some architectural patterns.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Refining the architecture context and architectural alternatives is done by performing the following RUP task (note&#xD;
    that other RUP tasks and artifacts of the business modeling and analysis &amp;amp; design disciplines may be applicable,&#xD;
    but this is the minimum recommended set):&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
